    "shortDescription": "A rooster doesn't crow just at dawn — he'll crow at anything unusual: a strange noise, a person walking past, or just because he feels like it. The crow is a territorial announcement, letting other roosters know who's in charge of this patch of ground. Fun fact: Roosters anticipate sunrise and start crowing slightly before it actually gets light."
